        "evidence": "<p>Addition of assigned points.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>5 independent items, each scored 0 (Absent), 1 (Intermediate), or 2 (Present)</li>\n<li>Minimum score = 0; maximum = 10</li>\n<li>Initial testing for &ldquo;Reflex Irritability&rdquo; was nasal and oropharyngeal suctioning with rubber catheter meant to elicit grimace, sneeze, or cough.\n<ul>\n<li>Later, a rapid, tangential slap of the sole of the foot was found to be an easier and more effective stimulus.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>",
        "facts": "<p><strong>Score interpretation:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Scores &ge;7; generally normal</li>\n<li>Score of 4 to 6; fairly low</li>\n<li>Scores &le;3; critically low, needs intervention</li>\n</ul>",
